Merge pull request #631 from jfinkels/case-insensitive-sorting

Allows client to request case-insensitive sorting

Adds more metadata in the schema view.

This commit adds collection name and primary key information for each
model in the root endpoint schema view.
added the info in meta/urls for now
Removes redundant entry in build matrix.
Removes redundant entry in build matrix.
Only test backport dependencies on Python 2
Adds Python 3.6 and 3.7-dev to Travis build
Refactors assoc. proxy helper function code
Makes all association proxy relationships visible
Removes unused import.
Support assoc. proxies in relationship endpoints
Removes over-indentation in continuation line
Adds documentation for association proxy setups.
Refactors function for deciding whether to exclude a field from serialization
Adds tests for updating resources.
Moves association proxy tests to their own module.
Adds tests for creating with association proxies.
Support association proxies in GET requests.
Removes unused import.

URL encodes first, last, prev, and next links.

Previously, Flask-Restless was not URL encoding the `first`, `last`,
`next`, and `prev` pagination links in the response JSON document. This
commit corrects that and additionally corrects some imprecise unit tests
that were not accounting for URL encoding.
Removes warning filter from testing code
Notes changes due to previous commits.

Refactors deserialization code

This commit makes the resource object deserializer and the resource
identifier object inherit from a common base class.
Makes deserialization more modular to facilitate refactoring.

Modularizes deserializer code.

Doing this also caught two bugs in existing tests, in which the
deserializer was accepting incorrectly formatted resource objects.
